WEBVTT

00:08.119 --> 00:10.204
[Phil] <i>Previously on</i> Roadies...

00:10.239 --> 00:11.772
Bill and Shelli.

00:11.807 --> 00:13.707
<i>That's like your parents having sex</i>

00:13.743 --> 00:16.410
<i>and cheating on each
other all at the same time.</i>

00:16.445 --> 00:18.579
How was your day? Tell me everything.

00:18.614 --> 00:20.397
Sean had someone hide

00:20.416 --> 00:22.349
a birthday gift for me in the seats.

00:22.385 --> 00:25.352
Right, congratulations. It's nice.

00:25.388 --> 00:26.603
It can't be true.

00:26.711 --> 00:28.917
People actually think that I'm...
I'm hooking up with Reg?

00:28.941 --> 00:31.975
Why don't you stab my fucking
eyes out and blind me

00:32.011 --> 00:34.956
so I no longer have to
witness this goddamn travesty?

00:35.084 --> 00:37.075
I find it incredibly
sexist that people think

00:37.099 --> 00:39.366
I'm making love to him in
his spendcentric socks.

00:39.402 --> 00:40.962
You worked with my
favorite band of all time,

00:40.986 --> 00:42.970
the original Lynyrd Skynyrd.

00:43.005 --> 00:46.240
This was given to me in 1976

00:46.275 --> 00:48.142
by Ronnie Van Zant,

00:48.177 --> 00:50.411
and I have not taken it off since.

00:50.446 --> 00:51.578
Who's Robbie Van Zant?

00:51.614 --> 00:53.147
[Phil] Who is Ronnie Van Zant?

00:53.182 --> 00:55.048
There's a tradition on this adventure,

00:55.084 --> 00:57.618
and you need to bone up on
whose shoulders you're standing on.

00:57.653 --> 01:02.623
You are invited to
leave the organization now.

01:02.658 --> 01:04.558
Let me just talk...

01:04.593 --> 01:06.593
About you firing me...

01:06.629 --> 01:08.128
Listen, Phil. I did not fire you.

01:08.164 --> 01:09.808
Preston fired you. I
was just the messenger.

01:09.832 --> 01:12.499
This is a... This is a very special day.

01:12.535 --> 01:13.767
[Phil] <i>Get on in here.</i>

01:13.803 --> 01:15.736
Get you some. God I missed you people.

01:15.771 --> 01:17.604
God I've missed you people.

01:19.335 --> 01:20.652
[bluesy music playing on phone]

01:20.676 --> 01:21.642
[knock at door]

01:21.677 --> 01:25.245
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:25.281 --> 01:26.947
[knock at door]

01:26.982 --> 01:31.385
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:35.291 --> 01:37.825
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:40.162 --> 01:41.762
Hey, front desk ain't answering, Bill.

01:41.797 --> 01:43.330
- Shit.
- Hey, come here.

01:43.365 --> 01:44.365
You got your cell on you?

01:44.400 --> 01:45.866
- Yeah.
- Okay.

01:45.901 --> 01:47.935
Okay, I need you to call the police.

01:47.970 --> 01:50.504
[touch-tones beeping]

01:50.539 --> 01:51.638
[pounding on door]

01:51.674 --> 01:52.940
Yeah, hey, I'm calling the cops

01:52.975 --> 01:54.808
about a possible
situation at the Marriott.

01:54.844 --> 01:56.810
You're... you're on the
phone with the cops now.

01:56.846 --> 01:58.345
- Uh, yeah, sorry.
- It's okay.

01:58.380 --> 02:01.782
- His name's Phil.
- Right, Phil Valentine.

02:01.817 --> 02:03.317
- Phil Valentine.
- Right.

02:03.352 --> 02:04.663
What the fuck is it that you want?

02:04.687 --> 02:06.620
- Oh, shit.
- Phil, put that down.

02:06.655 --> 02:07.721
You're alive.

02:07.756 --> 02:08.955
Of course I'm alive.

02:08.991 --> 02:10.524
My body wakes up when I'm needed.

02:10.559 --> 02:12.659
- Easy, White Buffalo.
- Jesus, did I oversleep?

02:12.695 --> 02:14.206
Yeah, we... we're all good. Phil's okay.

02:14.230 --> 02:15.507
- Yeah, you overslept.
- But thank you, cops.

02:15.531 --> 02:16.797
Hey, I'm on probation.

02:16.832 --> 02:18.148
What are you calling the cops for?

02:18.172 --> 02:19.978
- They're not coming.
- You weren't answering, man.

02:20.002 --> 02:21.368
Why is everybody freaking out?

02:21.403 --> 02:23.403
Is it... Is it daylight savings time?

02:23.439 --> 02:25.839
Phil, I-i-it is not daylight savings.

02:25.875 --> 02:27.241
That was two months ago.

02:27.276 --> 02:28.809
Shit.

02:28.844 --> 02:29.821
It's all right. [clears throat]

02:29.845 --> 02:31.345
Now, just listen to me, okay?

02:31.380 --> 02:34.414
There was a bomb scare at
Cory River Arena, okay?

02:34.450 --> 02:36.583
So we're gonna leave
early to get to San Diego

02:36.619 --> 02:38.585
for the Funko corporate
gig that Reg arranged.

02:38.621 --> 02:41.388
That limey douche bag motherfucker.

02:41.423 --> 02:44.024
He's actually turning
out to be not that bad.

02:44.059 --> 02:45.893
A rattlesnake makes
a pretty little noise

02:45.945 --> 02:47.928
before he sinks his
teeth into you, Bill.

02:47.963 --> 02:50.697
And a rattlesnake is
trained to do one thing,

02:50.733 --> 02:54.067
bite you, kill you,
and move the fuck on.

02:54.103 --> 02:56.053
Now, what time you need me on the bus?

02:56.088 --> 02:59.056
<i>[Tyler Lyle's "California" playing]</i>

02:59.091 --> 03:04.094
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:06.048 --> 03:11.034
<i>♪ I'm not sorry I fell in love ♪</i>

03:11.070 --> 03:13.804
<i>♪ I'm not sorry ♪</i>

03:13.839 --> 03:16.907
<i>♪ That you never cared enough ♪</i>

03:16.942 --> 03:21.912
<i>♪ It's just motion, it's just time ♪</i>

